docs.lead_paragraph: The World Health Organization (WHO) has begun assessing more than 120 potential treatments for Ebola patients, it said on Friday, but so far has found none that definitely work, and some that definitely do not.

headline.main: WHO Starts Survey of Ebola Treatments, Says None Proven So Far

headline.main: Cigna Agrees to Reduce H.I.V. Drug Costs for Some Florida Patients
headline.print_headline: Cigna Agrees to Reduce H.I.V. Drug Costs for Some Florida Patients

docs.abstract: Cigna agrees to reduce out-of-pocket costs that patients in Florida must pay for HIV drugs, settling complaint filed by advocacy groups who said drug pricing system in state's health care plans was discriminatory.
docs.snippet: Under the settlement with Florida regulators, the insurer will limit to $200 a month what patients have to pay for some commonly prescribed drugs..
